{{Dicdef}}

In [[biology]], '''heterolysis''' refers to [[apoptosis]] induced by hydrolytic enzymes from surrounding (usually inflammatory) cells. On the other hand, [[Autolysis (biology)|Autolysis]] is apoptosis of a cell by its own enzymes.

