The '''Malonate Uptake (MatC) family''' ([http://www.tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=2.A.101 TC# 2.A.101]) is a constituent of the [[Ion transporter|ion transporter (IT) superfamily]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Lolkema|first=Juke S.|last2=Slotboom|first2=Dirk Jan|date=2003-04-11|title=Classification of 29 families of secondary transport proteins into a single structural class using hydropathy profile analysis|journal=Journal of Molecular Biology|volume=327|issue=5|pages=901–909|issn=0022-2836|pmid=12662917|doi=10.1016/s0022-2836(03)00214-6|url=https://www.rug.nl/research/portal/files/6669967/2003JMolBiolLolkemaSupp.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Prakash|first=Shraddha|last2=Cooper|first2=Garret|last3=Singhi|first3=Soumya|last4=Saier|first4=Milton H.|date=2003-12-03|title=The ion transporter superfamily|journal=Biochimica et Biophysica Acta|volume=1618|issue=1|pages=79–92|issn=0006-3002|pmid=14643936|doi=10.1016/j.bbamem.2003.10.010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Rabus|first=R.|last2=Jack|first2=D. L.|last3=Kelly|first3=D. J.|last4=Saier|first4=M. H.|date=1999-12-01|title=TRAP transporters: an ancient family of extracytoplasmic solute-receptor-dependent secondary active transporters|journal=Microbiology|volume=145|pages=3431–3445|doi=10.1099/00221287-145-12-3431|issn=1350-0872|pmid=10627041|issue=12}}</ref> It consists of proteins from [[Gram-negative bacteria|Gram-negative]] and [[Gram-positive bacteria]] (e.g., [[Xanthomonas]], [[Rhizobium]] and [[Streptomyces]] species), simple eukaryotes (e.g., ''[[Chlamydomonas reinhardtii]]'') and archaea (e.g., ''[[Methanococcus Jannaschii|Methanococcus jannaschii]]''). The proteins are of about 450 amino acyl residues in length with 12-14 putative transmembrane segments (TMSs). Closest functionally-characterized homologues are in the [[Divalent anion-Sodium symporter|DASS]] ([http://www.tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=2.A.47 TC #2.A.47]) family. One member of this family is a putative [[malonate]] transporter (MatC of ''[[Rhizobium leguminosarum]]'' [[Rhizobium leguminosarum|bv ''trifolii'']], [http://www.tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=2.A.101.1.2 TC# 2.A.101.1.2]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=2.A.101|title=2.A.101 The Malonate Uptake (MatC) Family (Formerly UIT1)|website=Transporter Classification Database|access-date=2016-03-03}}</ref>

