The '''Basic Amino Acid Antiporter (ArcD) family''' (TC# 2.A.118) is a constituent of the [[Ion transporter|IT superfamily]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lolkema|first=Juke S.|last2=Slotboom|first2=Dirk Jan|date=2003-04-11|title=Classification of 29 families of secondary transport proteins into a single structural class using hydropathy profile analysis|journal=Journal of Molecular Biology|volume=327|issue=5|pages=901–909|issn=0022-2836|pmid=12662917|doi=10.1016/s0022-2836(03)00214-6|url=https://pure.rug.nl/ws/files/6669968/2003JMolBiolLolkema.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Prakash|first=Shraddha|last2=Cooper|first2=Garret|last3=Singhi|first3=Soumya|last4=Saier|first4=Milton H.|date=2003-12-03|title=The ion transporter superfamily|journal=Biochimica et Biophysica Acta|volume=1618|issue=1|pages=79–92|issn=0006-3002|pmid=14643936|doi=10.1016/j.bbamem.2003.10.010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Rabus|first=R.|last2=Jack|first2=D. L.|last3=Kelly|first3=D. J.|last4=Saier|first4=M. H.|date=1999-12-01|title=TRAP transporters: an ancient family of extracytoplasmic solute-receptor-dependent secondary active transporters|journal=Microbiology|volume=145 ( Pt 12)|issue=12|pages=3431–3445|doi=10.1099/00221287-145-12-3431|issn=1350-0872|pmid=10627041}}</ref> This family consists of proteins from [[Gram-negative bacteria|Gram-negative]] and [[Gram-positive bacteria]] (e.g., ''[[Streptococcus]]'', ''[[Escherichia]]'', ''[[Salmonella]]'', ''[[Fusobacterium]]'' and ''[[Borrelia]]'' species). The proteins are of about 480 amino acyl residues (aas) in length and have 10-12 putative transmembrane segments (TMSs). Functionally characterized homologues are in the DcuC ([http://www.tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=2.A.61 TC #2.A.61]) and ArsB ([http://www.tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=2.A.4 TC #2.A.4]) families. Some members of the family probably catalyze arginine/ornithine or citruline/ornithine antiport.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gupta|first=Radha|last2=Yang|first2=Jun|last3=Dong|first3=Yimin|last4=Swiatlo|first4=Edwin|last5=Zhang|first5=Jing-Ren|last6=Metzger|first6=Dennis W.|last7=Bai|first7=Guangchun|date=2013-10-01|title=Deletion of arcD in Streptococcus pneumoniae D39 impairs its capsule and attenuates virulence|journal=Infection and Immunity|volume=81|issue=10|pages=3903–3911|doi=10.1128/IAI.00778-13|issn=1098-5522|pmc=3811789|pmid=23918778}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Rimaux|first=Tom|last2=Rivière|first2=Audrey|last3=Hebert|first3=Elvira María|last4=Mozzi|first4=Fernanda|last5=Weckx|first5=Stefan|last6=De Vuyst|first6=Luc|last7=Leroy|first7=Frédéric|date=2013-04-01|title=A putative transport protein is involved in citrulline excretion and re-uptake during arginine deiminase pathway activity by Lactobacillus sakei|journal=Research in Microbiology|volume=164|issue=3|pages=216–225|doi=10.1016/j.resmic.2012.11.004|issn=1769-7123|pmid=23178175}}</ref>
