The concentration of [[calcium]] in the [[cell nucleus]] can increase in response to signals from the environment. '''Nuclear calcium''' is an evolutionary conserved potent regulator of [[gene expression]] that allows cells to undergo long-lasting adaptive responses. The 'Nuclear Calcium Hypothesis’ by Hilmar Bading describes nuclear calcium in neurons as an important signaling end-point in [[synapse]]-to-nucleus communication that activates gene expression programs needed for persistent adaptations.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bading|first=H.|date=2000-09-01|title=Transcription-dependent neuronal plasticity: the nuclear calcium hypothesis|journal=European Journal of Biochemistry / FEBS|volume=267|issue=17|pages=5280–5283|doi=10.1046/j.1432-1327.2000.01565.x|issn=0014-2956|pmid=10951185}}</ref> In the [[nervous system]], nuclear calcium is required for [[long-term memory]] formation, [[acquired neuroprotection]], and the development of chronic inflammatory pain.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Weislogel|first=Jan-Marek|last2=Bengtson|first2=C. Peter|last3=Müller|first3=Michaela K.|last4=Hörtzsch|first4=Jan N.|last5=Bujard|first5=Martina|last6=Schuster|first6=Christoph M.|last7=Bading|first7=Hilmar|date=2013-05-07|title=Requirement for nuclear calcium signaling in Drosophila long-term memory|journal=Science Signaling|volume=6|issue=274|pages=ra33|doi=10.1126/scisignal.2003598|issn=1937-9145|pmid=23652205}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Zhang|first=Sheng-Jia|last2=Zou|first2=Ming|last3=Lu|first3=Li|last4=Lau|first4=David|last5=Ditzel|first5=Désirée A. W.|last6=Delucinge-Vivier|first6=Celine|last7=Aso|first7=Yoshinori|last8=Descombes|first8=Patrick|last9=Bading|first9=Hilmar|date=2009-08-01|title=Nuclear calcium signaling controls expression of a large gene pool: identification of a gene program for acquired neuroprotection induced by synaptic activity|journal=PLOS Genetics|volume=5|issue=8|pages=e1000604|doi=10.1371/journal.pgen.1000604|issn=1553-7404|pmc=2718706|pmid=19680447}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Simonetti|first=Manuela|last2=Hagenston|first2=Anna M.|last3=Vardeh|first3=Daniel|last4=Freitag|first4=H. Eckehard|last5=Mauceri|first5=Daniela|last6=Lu|first6=Jianning|last7=Satagopam|first7=Venkata P.|last8=Schneider|first8=Reinhard|last9=Costigan|first9=Michael|date=2013-01-09|title=Nuclear calcium signaling in spinal neurons drives a genomic program required for persistent inflammatory pain|journal=Neuron|volume=77|issue=1|pages=43–57|doi=10.1016/j.neuron.2012.10.037|issn=1097-4199|pmc=3593630|pmid=23312515}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bading|first=Hilmar|title=Nuclear calcium signalling in the regulation of brain function|journal=Nature Reviews Neuroscience|volume=14|issue=9|pages=593–608|doi=10.1038/nrn3531|pmid=23942469|year=2013}}</ref> In the heart, nuclear calcium is important for the development of cardiac [[hypertrophy]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Higazi|first=Daniel R.|last2=Fearnley|first2=Claire J.|last3=Drawnel|first3=Faye M.|last4=Talasila|first4=Amarnath|last5=Corps|first5=Elaine M.|last6=Ritter|first6=Oliver|last7=McDonald|first7=Fraser|last8=Mikoshiba|first8=Katsuhiko|last9=Bootman|first9=Martin D.|date=2009-02-27|title=Endothelin-1-stimulated InsP3-induced Ca2+ release is a nexus for hypertrophic signaling in cardiac myocytes|journal=Molecular Cell|volume=33|issue=4|pages=472–482|doi=10.1016/j.molcel.2009.02.005|issn=1097-4164|pmid=19250908}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Guatimosim|first=Silvia|last2=Amaya|first2=Maria Jimena|last3=Guerra|first3=Mateus T.|last4=Aguiar|first4=Carla J.|last5=Goes|first5=Alfredo M.|last6=Gómez-Viquez|first6=Norma Leticia|last7=Rodrigues|first7=Michele A.|last8=Gomes|first8=Dawidson A.|last9=Martins-Cruz|first9=Juliana|date=2008-08-01|title=Nuclear Ca2+ regulates cardiomyocyte function|journal=Cell Calcium|volume=44|issue=2|pages=230–242|doi=10.1016/j.ceca.2007.11.016|issn=0143-4160|pmid=18201761}}</ref> In the immune system, nuclear calcium is required for human T cell activation.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Monaco|first=Sara|last2=Jahraus|first2=Beate|last3=Samstag|first3=Yvonne|last4=Bading|first4=Hilmar|date=2016-10-24|title=Nuclear calcium is required for human T cell activation|url=http://jcb.rupress.org/content/215/2/231|journal=J Cell Biol|language=en|volume=215|issue=2|pages=231–243|doi=10.1083/jcb.201602001|issn=0021-9525|pmc=5084645|pmid=27810914}}</ref> Plants use nuclear calcium to control [[symbiosis]] signaling.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Oldroyd|first=Giles E. D.|last2=Downie|first2=J. Allan|date=2006-08-01|title=Nuclear calcium changes at the core of symbiosis signalling|journal=Current Opinion in Plant Biology|volume=9|issue=4|pages=351–357|doi=10.1016/j.pbi.2006.05.003|issn=1369-5266|pmid=16713329}}</ref>
