{{featured portal|FPOCyear=2007}}

{{Cat main|Music theory}}
{{Commons cat|Music theory}}

'''Music theory''' is a set of systems for analyzing, classifying, and composing music and the elements of [[music]]. Narrowly it may be defined as the description in words of elements of music, and the interrelationship toward the [[music notation|notation]] of music and performance practice. Broadly, theory may be considered any statement, belief, or concept of the music ([[Benjamin Boretz|Boretz]], 1995). Thus academic study of music is called [[musicology]].

{{DEFAULTSORT:Theory, Music}}
[[Category:Music]]
[[Category:Music history]]
[[Category:Musicology]]

[[Musicology]] is the academic study of [[music]]. [[List of musicologists|Musicologists]] may study quite a wide range of subjects. Some, for instance, may specialize in [[England|English]] [[Tudor dynasty|Tudor]] church music, others in the history of [[musical notation]] and others in the development of the [[flute]].

